–1464","1415–1506":"1415–1506","1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1423":"1423","1422":"1422","1464":"1464","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1506":"1506","Ireland":"Ireland","County Cavan, Ireland":"County Cavan, Ireland","County Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Ireland","Polestown, Kilkenny, Ireland":"Powerstown, County Kilkenny, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Reilly","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Mairead, Aidan, Colm, Declan, Dermot, Dympna, Eamon, Finbar, Brennan, Brian Patrick, Brid.","Irish (Cavan, Meath): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>, a personal name of unexplained etymology. This is the name of a chieftain family in County Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Reilly","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Brennan, Brigid, Ciaran, Conor, Kieran, Aidan, Aileen, Caitlin, Clancy, Colm, Conn.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b>, see   O'Reilly  ."]},{"name":"O'Riley","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Eamonn.","Irish: variant of   O'Reilly  ."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["equivalent of   Katherine  , also occasionally used in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  T